<p>
<seg id=1> Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, who was visiting America, and Secretary of State Jim Bennett jointly held a press conference on the 29th in Washington, and they gave speeches on the Sino-American relationship. </seg>
<seg id=2> Tang Jiaxuan mentioned that the personal affairs of President Clinton were the internal affairs of America; China would never forget what President Clinton had done for the improvement of the Sino-American friendship. </seg>
<seg id=3> The following was the report of the press conference that day by the reporter of the Voice of America Zhou Youkang. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Hello everyone! American President Clinton met Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, who was visiting America, at 11am on the 29th in the White House. </seg>
<seg id=5> At the press conference jointly held by Jim Bennett and Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan at noon on the 29th in Washington, Secretary of State Jim Bennett announced the news that President Clinton would meet Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan. </seg>
<seg id=6> Jim Bennett said, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Secretary of State Jim Bennett said: " I am very happy to tell all of you that President Clinton met Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan just now, and they announced that China will sign the International Treaty of Citizen's Rights and Political Rights on 5 October in New York". </seg>
<seg id=8> At the press conference, Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said, " it's of significance to meet Clinton. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> President Clinton met me, and I think our meeting has achieved remarkable success". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> At present, President Clinton is in an eventful period, and many people in America and abroad showed their dissatisfaction and criticized him because of his love affairs. </seg>
<seg id=11> Some wanted to impeach him; some wanted him to fall from power; some Congressmen of Guomingdang even wanted to draw a clear line with him. </seg>
<seg id=12> However, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan didn't evade the issue, and he highly praised what President Clinton had done for the improvement of the Sino-American friendship. </seg>
<seg id=13> At the press conference, Tang Jiaxuan was asked whether the love affairs of President Clinton would affect the Sino-American relationship. </seg>
<seg id=14> Tang Jiaxuan answered like this: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=15> "I think it only concerns the Americans. </seg>
<seg id=16> I never think it will affect the relationship with China. </seg>
<seg id=17> President Clinton has made an important and precious contribution to the development of the Sino-America relationship, and we will never forget what he has done. </seg>
<seg id=18> For me, and for the Chinese people, I hope from the bottom of my heart that the Sino-America relationship will advance practically and steadily on the basis of the three joint communiques and the joint statement of the leaders of the two countries". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=19> The Chinese government has emphasized frequently that Taiwan is a province of China, and the issue of Taiwan is purely a Chinese internal affair. </seg>
<seg id=20> At the Conference of the United Nations and many public occasions in Washington, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan kept on talking about the issue of Taiwan. </seg>
<seg id=21> At the press conference, a reporter asked Tang Jiaxuan about the biggest barriers for the Sino-American relationship as strategic partners. Tang Jiaxuan said: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=22> "I think we have mentioned many times that we should pay more attention to how to solve the issue of Taiwan. </seg>
<seg id=23> The reason is that the issue of Taiwan is the most sensitive and practical matter of the Sino-American relationship. </seg>
</p>
